[13:31:25    63] - Directly allocating numeric array nodes with `cJSON_New_Item(&raw mut global_hooks)` failed `check-unsafe2`; use existing constructor functions for global-hook allocation unless the target function already uses `global_hooks`.
[13:31:25    63] - `find-unsafe2` panicked on both `impl IntoIterator` and a generic `IntoIterator` helper. Prefer monomorphic helper shapes if a helper is necessary.
[13:31:25    63] - Avoid putting unsafe conversions in closures inside exported FFI functions; previous notes indicate `check-unsafe2` can treat those closures as implementation code.
[13:31:25    63] - Preserve existing null-check order when converting raw pointers to references or `CStr`.
[13:31:25    63] - No `.git` directory is available in `/root/work`; use direct file inspection rather than git diff/status.
[13:31:25    63] - In `get_array_item`, using `array.child.as_ref()` / `child.next.as_ref()` failed because unsafe calls increased from 0 to 2. The accepted version keeps a safe signature but uses one raw deref expression in the loop.
[13:31:25    63] - Ordinary `Box<cJSON>` for parser nodes is not behavior-preserving while `cJSON_Delete` frees nodes through cJSON hooks/custom allocators. Keep custom allocator ownership intact unless allocation/deallocation is migrated together.
[13:31:25    63] 
